{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddcfabfa6-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s2006"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2006"},"text":"§ 2006.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Withdrawal by Representative of request for vacant rooms","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A Representative or Representative-elect making request for the assignment of a vacant room may withdraw the same at any time and no one shall have pending at the same time more than one such request. The assignment of a new room to a Representative, upon his request, or the appointment of any Representative having an individual office room as chairman of a committee having a committee room, shall act as a relinquishment by him of the room previously assigned to him.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddcfabfa7-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1908-05-28"},"text":"May 28, 1908","children":[],"tail":", No. 30, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/35/578"},"text":"35 Stat. 578","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddcfabfa8-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddcfabfa9-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"iddcfabfaa-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was classified to section 179 of former Title 40, prior to the enactment of Title 40, Public Buildings, 